{
  "texts": [
    "The task involves the optimization of a trade-off between multimodal integration and the uniqueness of each modality.",
    "This balance is achieved through the evaluation of the distance metrics D p and D m, which are calculated as follows:D i p = F -C i p 2 2(7)D i m = F -C i m 2 2 (8)where F is the feature vector, and ∥•∥ 2 2 denotes the L2 norm.",
    "Furthermore, a balance is sought between the preservation of modalityspecific characteristics and the fusion process.",
    "This is expressed through the balance coefficient α, determined by:α i = D i n -D i p D i p + ϵ(9)where D i n is the norm distance, D i p is the positive class distance, and ϵ is a small constant to prevent division by zero.",
    "In the context of error minimization, the enhancement of the core tensor aims to address the bias inherent in the fusion process."
  ]
}